title: Henin, Safin nominated for International Tennis Hall of Fame
text: Photo: LIONEL CIRONNEAU, AP FILE - In this June 9, 2007, file photo, Belgium's Justine Henin poses with the trophy after beating Serbia's Ana Ivanovic in the women's final match of the French Open tennis tournament at Roland Garros stadium in Paris. Justine Henin and Marat Safin, who each won multiple Grand Slam titles and reached a No. 1 ranking, were nominated Friday, Oct. 23, 2015, for the International Tennis Hall of Fame. FILE - In this June 9, 2007, file photo, Belgium's Justine Henin... NEWPORT, R.I. (AP) — Justine Henin and Marat Safin, who each won multiple Grand Slam titles and reached a No. 1 ranking, were nominated Friday for the International Tennis Hall of Fame.
